Page 5 of http://www.statslab.cam.ac.uk/~rrw1/oc/oc2013.pdf

An investor starts with an initial capital of $x_1$ dollars. Each year, he
consumes part of his capital and invests the rest, which grows at a rate of
interest $a$. Thus, if his capital in year $t$ was $x_t$, then his capital in
year $t+1$ is
$$ x_{t+1} = x_t + a(x_t - u_t). $$
